-*- text -*-

Freesurfer compilation/installation
===================================

If you have /usr/pubsw/packages, then you only do

./configure --prefix=$installdir
./make
./make install

(if you do not specify prefix, then the install directory is /usr/local,
 which you may not have rights to install.)

If you have mni installed somewhere, then you change the configure line to:

./configure --prefix=$installdir --with-mni-dir=$mnidir

You can see all the options by 

./configure --help

Please send email to tosa@nmr.mgh.harvard.edu if you have problems.


MacOSX Panther specific
=======================

Dependent libraries:

MNI tools: download the package for Panther from MNI.

You should use "fink" to install glut, tix, BLT libraries.
(Unfortunately tix is unstable package. Read fink web page on 
 how to install the unstable package.)

ln -s /sw/lib/libBLT24.dylib /sw/lib/libBLT.dylib
setenv CFLAGS "-g -O2 -I/sw/include"
setenv CXXFLAGS "-g -O2 -I/sw/include"
setenv LDFLAGS "-L/sw/include"

Configuration

comment out  
   AC_TOOL_CHECK(AR, true) 
in aclocal.m4

$ automake -v 
  make sure that there is no error.

$ autoconf

$ configure --prefix=(somewhere) --with-mni-dir=/usr/local/mni --x-includes=/usr/X11R6/include

